{"title_page": "Our Research", "text_new": "{{Infobox non-profit\n| name                = Our Research\n| logo                = Ourresearch logo.png\n| logo_alt            = Logo of Our Research\n| logo_caption        = Logo of Our Research.\n| formation           = {{start date and age|2011}}<ref name=\"Else2018\">{{cite journal |last1=Else |first1=Holly |title=How Unpaywall is transforming open science |journal=Nature |date=15 August 2018 |volume=560 |issue=7718 |pages=290\u2013291 |doi=10.1038/D41586-018-05968-3}}</ref>\n| founder             = Jason Priem, <br/>Heather Piwowar\n| founding_location   = \n| type                = Nonprofit Organization\n| tax_id              = 46-1599252\n| registration_id     = <!-- for non-profit org -->\n| status              = [[501(c)(3) organization]]\n| headquarters        = [[Stanford]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.guidestar.org/profile/46-1599252|title=Entry of Impactstory in GuideStar|last=|first=|date=|website=www.guidestar.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n| location            = [[Vancouver]]\n| products            = \n| services            = unpaywall, ImpactStory, depsy, ...\n| website             = {{URL|https://our-research.org/}}\n| formerly            = ImpactStory\n}}\n\n\n'''Our Research''', formerly named ImpactStory, is a [[nonprofit organization]], which creates and distribute tools and services for the research community. They are following open practices with their data (to the extent allowed by providers' terms of service), code,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://github.com/total-impact|title=ImpactStory total-impact|work=GitHub|accessdate=1 January 2014}}</ref> and governance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.impactstory.org/2012/03/01/18535014681/|title=Sloan Foundation grant submitted|date=1 March 2012|work=ImpactStory blog|accessdate=1 January 2014}}</ref> Our Research was funded by the [[Alfred P. Sloan Foundation]]<ref>{{cite web|title=About|url=http://impactstory.org/about|work=ImpactStory|accessdate=1 January 2014}}</ref> and the [[National Science Foundation]].<ref>{{cite web|title=ImpactStory awarded $300k NSF grant!|url=http://blog.impactstory.org/2013/09/27/impactstory-awarded-300k-nsf-grant/|work=ImpactStory|accessdate=2 January 2014}}</ref>\n\n==ImpactStory==\n\nImpactStory is the first produced [[open source]], web-based tool by Our Research. It provides [[altmetrics]] to help researchers measure the impacts of their research outputs including journal articles, [[Blog|blog posts]], datasets, and software.<ref>{{cite web|last=Priem|first=Jason|title=The launch of ImpactStory: using altmetrics to tell data-driven stories|url=http://blogs.lse.ac.uk/impactofsocialsciences/2012/09/25/the-launch-of-impactstor/|work=Impact of Social Sciences|publisher=LSE|accessdate=1 January 2014|author2=Heather Piwowar|date=25 September 2012}}</ref> This aims to change the focus of the scholarly reward system to value and encourage web-native scholarship.\n\nIt provides context to its metrics so that they are meaningful without knowledge of the specific dataset: for example, instead of letting the reader guess whether having five [[Fork (software development)|forks]] on [[GitHub]] is common, ImpactStory would tell that the repository is in the 95th percentile of all GitHub repositories created that year.<ref>{{cite web|title=ImpactStory adds figshare integration|url=http://www.researchinformation.info/news/news_story.php?news_id=1443|work=Research Information|accessdate=1 January 2014|date=3 December 2013}}</ref>\n\nThe metrics provided by ImpactStory can be used by researchers who want to know how many times their work has been downloaded and shared,<ref>{{cite web|last=Eisen|first=Jonathan|title=Playing with Impact Story to look at Alt Metrics for my papers, data, etc |url=http://phylogenomics.blogspot.co.uk/2012/11/playing-with-impact-story-to-look-at.html|work=The Tree of Life|accessdate=1 January 2014|date=29 November 2012}}</ref> and also research funders who are interested in the impact of research beyond only considering citations to journal articles.\n\n==Unpaywall==\nOne of the solutions Our Research developed is [http://unpaywall.org Unpaywall], a [[browser extension]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Coldewey |first1=Devin |title=Unpaywall scours the web for free versions of scientific papers |url=https://techcrunch.com/2017/04/05/unpaywall-scours-the-web-for-free-versions-of-scientific-papers/ |website=TechCrunch |accessdate=16 August 2018}}</ref> which finds free versions of (paywalled) articles.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Chawla |first1=Dalmeet Singh |title=Unpaywall finds free versions of paywalled papers |journal=Nature |date=4 April 2017 |doi=10.1038/nature.2017.21765}}</ref> In July 2018 it was reported to provide free access to 20 million articles,<ref name=\"Else2018\"/> and about 47% of the articles that people search with Unpaywall.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Doctorow |first1=Cory |title=Unpaywall: a search-engine for authorized, freely accessible versions of scholarly journal articles / Boing Boing |url=https://boingboing.net/2018/02/06/search-engine-arbitrage.html |website=boingboing.net}}</ref> In June 2017 it was integrated into [[Web of Science]] and in July 2018 [[Elsevier]] announced plans the same month to integrate the service into the [[Scopus]] search engine.<ref name=\"Else2018\"/>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[https://our-research.org/ Official website]\n*[https://unpaywall.org/ Unpaywall website]\n\n[[Category:Non-profit organizations]]\n[[Category:Bibliometrics]]\n[[Category:Scholarly communication]]\n[[Category:Academic publishing]]\n[[Category:Internet properties established in 2011]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox non-profit\n| name                = Our Research\n| logo                = Ourresearch logo.png\n| logo_alt            = Logo of Our Research\n| logo_caption        = Logo of Our Research.\n| formation           = {{start date and age|2011}}<ref name=\"Else2018\">{{cite journal |last1=Else |first1=Holly |title=How Unpaywall is transforming open science |journal=Nature |date=15 August 2018 |volume=560 |issue=7718 |pages=290\u2013291 |doi=10.1038/D41586-018-05968-3}}</ref>\n| founder             = Jason Priem, <br/>Heather Piwowar\n| founding_location   = \n| type                = Nonprofit Organization\n| tax_id              = 46-1599252\n| registration_id     = <!-- for non-profit org -->\n| status              = [[501(c)(3) organization]]\n| headquarters        = [[Stanford]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.guidestar.org/profile/46-1599252|title=Entry of Impactstory in GuideStar|last=|first=|date=|website=www.guidestar.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n| location            = [[Vancouver]]\n| products            = \n| services            = unpaywall, ImpactStory, depsy, ...\n| website             = {{URL|https://our-research.org/}}\n| formerly            = ImpactStory\n}}\n\n\n'''Our Research''', formerly named ImpactStory, is a [[nonprofit organization]], which creates and distribute tools and services for the research community. They are following open practices with their data (to the extent allowed by providers' terms of service), code,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://github.com/total-impact|title=ImpactStory total-impact|work=GitHub|accessdate=1 January 2014}}</ref> and governance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.impactstory.org/2012/03/01/18535014681/|title=Sloan Foundation grant submitted|date=1 March 2012|work=ImpactStory blog|accessdate=1 January 2014}}</ref> Our Research was funded by the [[Alfred P. Sloan Foundation]]<ref>{{cite web|title=About|url=http://impactstory.org/about|work=ImpactStory|accessdate=1 January 2014}}</ref> and the [[National Science Foundation]].<ref>{{cite web|title=ImpactStory awarded $300k NSF grant!|url=http://blog.impactstory.org/2013/09/27/impactstory-awarded-300k-nsf-grant/|work=ImpactStory|accessdate=2 January 2014}}</ref>\n\n==ImpactStory==\n\nImpactStory is the first produced [[open source]], web-based tool by Our Research. It provides [[altmetrics]] to help researchers measure the impacts of their research outputs including journal articles, [[Blog|blog posts]], datasets, and software.<ref>{{cite web|last=Priem|first=Jason|title=The launch of ImpactStory: using altmetrics to tell data-driven stories|url=http://blogs.lse.ac.uk/impactofsocialsciences/2012/09/25/the-launch-of-impactstor/|work=Impact of Social Sciences|publisher=LSE|accessdate=1 January 2014|author2=Heather Piwowar|date=25 September 2012}}</ref> This aims to change the focus of the scholarly reward system to value and encourage web-native scholarship.\n\nIt provides context to its metrics so that they are meaningful without knowledge of the specific dataset: for example, instead of letting the reader guess whether having five [[Fork (software development)|forks]] on [[GitHub]] is common, ImpactStory would tell that the repository is in the 95th percentile of all GitHub repositories created that year.<ref>{{cite web|title=ImpactStory adds figshare integration|url=http://www.researchinformation.info/news/news_story.php?news_id=1443|work=Research Information|accessdate=1 January 2014|date=3 December 2013}}</ref>\n\nThe metrics provided by ImpactStory can be used by researchers who want to know how many times their work has been downloaded and shared,<ref>{{cite web|last=Eisen|first=Jonathan|title=Playing with Impact Story to look at Alt Metrics for my papers, data, etc |url=http://phylogenomics.blogspot.co.uk/2012/11/playing-with-impact-story-to-look-at.html|work=The Tree of Life|accessdate=1 January 2014|date=29 November 2012}}</ref> and also research funders who are interested in the impact of research beyond only considering citations to journal articles.\n\n==Unpaywall==\nOne of the solutions Our Research developed is [http://unpaywall.org Unpaywall], a [[browser extension]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Coldewey |first1=Devin |title=Unpaywall scours the web for free versions of scientific papers |url=https://techcrunch.com/2017/04/05/unpaywall-scours-the-web-for-free-versions-of-scientific-papers/ |website=TechCrunch |accessdate=16 August 2018}}</ref> which finds free versions of (paywalled) articles.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Chawla |first1=Dalmeet Singh |title=Unpaywall finds free versions of paywalled papers |journal=Nature |date=4 April 2017 |doi=10.1038/nature.2017.21765}}</ref> In July 2018 it was reported to provide free access to 20 million articles,<ref name=\"Else2018\"/> and about 47% of the articles that people search with Unpaywall.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Doctorow |first1=Cory |title=Unpaywall: a search-engine for authorized, freely accessible versions of scholarly journal articles / Boing Boing |url=https://boingboing.net/2018/02/06/search-engine-arbitrage.html |website=boingboing.net}}</ref> In June 2017 it was integrated into [[Web of Science]] and in July 2018 [[Elsevier]] announced plans the same month to integrate the service into the [[Scopus]] search engine.<ref name=\"Else2018\"/>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[https://our-research.org/ Official website]\n*[https://unpaywall.org/ Unpaywall website]\n\n[[Category:Nonprofit organization]]\n[[Category:Bibliometrics]]\n[[Category:Scholarly communication]]\n[[Category:Academic publishing]]\n[[Category:Internet properties established in 2011]]\n", "name_user": "Zuphilip", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Our_Research"}
{"title_page": "2006\u201307 Brighton & Hove Albion F.C. season", "text_new": "{{Infobox football club season\n | club               = [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]]\n | season             = 2006-2007\n | manager            = [[Mark McGhee]] (until 8 September 2006)<br>[[Dean Wilkins]] (from 8 September 2006)\n | league             = [[EFL League One|League One]]\n | league result      = 18th\n | chairman           = [[Dick Knight (businessman)|Dick Knight]]\n | cup1               = [[FA Cup]]\n | cup1 result        = Third Round vs [[West Ham United]]\n | cup2               = [[Football League Cup|League Cup]]\n | cup2 result        = Second Round vs [[Southend United]]\n | cup3               = [[Football League Trophy]]\n | cup3 result        = Area Final vs [[Bristol City F.C.|Bristol City]]\n |prevseason=[[2005-06 Brighton & Hove Albion F.C. season|2005-06]]\n |nextseason=[[2007-08 Brighton & Hove Albion F.C. season|2007-08]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2006-07 season''' was [[Brighton & Hove Albion]]'s 105th year in existence and first season in [[EFL League One|League One]] after being relegated from the [[EFL Championship|Championship]].[[Mark McGhee]] began the season as manager, but after losing three consecutive matches he left the club on 8 September 2006.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/b/brighton/5326320.stm|title=Brighton boss McGhee leaves club|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> McGhee was succeeded as manager by youth coach and former Seagulls player [[Dean Wilkins]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/b/brighton/5393736.stm|title=Brighton confirm Wilkins as manager|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> who steered the side to an 18th-placed finish.\n\n==Squad==\n[http://www.footballsquads.co.uk/eng/2005-2006/flcham/brighton.htm]\n{{fs start}}\n{{Fs player|no=2|nat=AUS|pos=DF|name=[[Paul Reid (footballer born 1979)|Paul Reid]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=3|nat=ENG|pos=DF|name=[[Kerry Mayo]]}}\n{{Fs pl